  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. This package contains a targeted W-EP-03 weakness: the primary material-property dataset carries a dataVintage predating the model's most recent revision by several weeks; the narrative argues the revision was not material to the dataset's applicability, but no formal re-validation was performed.",
